cu500 | 1 | The surahs are separated by a double line drawn in the same ink, using no more than the space of one line.  Above this double line, written in light red ink without any strokes or dots and in a smaller and apparently later hand, are the title and verse count of the surah following.  Four short strokes that might easily be mistaken for dots mark the end of each verse.  A circle enclosing 2-4 dots and itself encircled by a number of dots marks off 10-verse groups in recto 8 and 15.  In verso 10, there are strokes instead of dots within the circle, with strokes and dots surrounding it.  These 3 10-verse divisions mark off verses 10, 20, and 40 of Surah 50 in the manuscript; these are, however, verses 10, 19, and 42 in the printed text.
