cu500_lin | 1 | On recto and verso: 20 lines each in Arabic
cu500_pal | 1 | The recto and verso show different Meccan scripts.  That of the recto is heavier and more angular; that of the verso is not only lighter but also less crowded and more graceful, resembling in many respects that of O.I. A6959 and O.I. A6990.  Vowel points are missing.  Diacritical dots are used on the recto and are placed the same as strokes would have been (as in O.I. A6975a).  To all appearances, the same pen that was used here for the text was used for the dots also.  The diacritical marks are used more freely on the recto than the verso.
